reasonable doubt what every veteran <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">policeman</ENAMEX> knows: Most <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">prisoners</ENAMEX> are
not petty, nonviolent <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">thieves</ENAMEX> or mere first-time, low-level drug
<ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">offenders</ENAMEX>. Yet, most of these hardened <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">criminals</ENAMEX> are still paroled well before
they have served out their latest sentence behind bars. On <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">any given day</TIMEX> in
<ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">America</ENAMEX>, there are <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">three</NUMEX> convicted <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">adult criminals</ENAMEX> out on probation or parole
for every one in <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">prison</ENAMEX>--and many of these are indistinguishable (in terms of
